If we make a request to h2.com, we'll get the request on worker2:

    >>> app3 = webtest.TestApp(lb.handle_wsgi)
    >>> g3 = gevent.spawn(app3.get, '/hi.html', {}, [('Host', 'h2.com')])

    >>> rno, env3 = read_message(worker2)
    >>> rno
    1
    >>> pprint(env3)
    {'HTTP_HOST': 'h2.com',
     'PATH_INFO': '/hi.html',
     'QUERY_STRING': '',
     'REQUEST_METHOD': 'GET',
     'SCRIPT_NAME': '',
